Dear Avocarrotians,
The bidder server was implemented in node.js version v7.10.1.
For mocking up the server I have used postman
For tests i have used mocha 1.20.1 suites.

1.Install nodejs and npm running the following:    
--> sudo apt-get update
--> sudo apt-get install curl
--> curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_7.x | sudo -E bash -
--> sudo apt-get install -y nodejs
--> sudo apt-get install npm


For starting the server:
 -- $nodejs bidder_server

For running tests :
#Optional timeout flag only in case of timeout thrown 
#exception due to async func call
 -- $mocha --timeout 5000 test/test_response_bid.js
